history.content:
Never mind. Found the answer:

* You must remain in at least 12 units, unless you are graduating this semester or have been approved for a reduced course load. 

* You must remain in at least 2 technical courses that fulfill remaining requirements for your engineering major unless you have completed all of your technical major/degree requirements.

I would like to use my late drop to drop a technical class soon. It's not a required class and this is my last semester so I have everything to graduate right now. My question is, if I drop this class, I'll go down to 10 units total, of which only 6 are technical... am I allowed to do this? Will it cause any problems with graduation?
history.subject: Late drop a technical course
